 other once-new technologies continue to inform our contemporarythinking. With insightful analysis, FeelingMediated explores a series of fascinating arguments about technology andemotion that became especially heated during the early 20th century. These debates, which carried forward andtransformed earlier discussions of technology and emotion, culminated in a setof ideas that became institutionalized in the structures of American mediaproduction, advertising, social research, and policy, leaving a lasting impact onour everyday lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jun 2020) 0aCommunication and technologyxHistoryxUnited States. 0aCommunication and technologyzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aCommunicationxPsychological aspectsxUnited States. 0aCommunicationxPsychological aspects. 0aMass media and culturexUnited States. 0aMass media and culturezUnited States. 0aMass media and technologyxHistoryxUnited States. 0aMass media and technologyzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aMass mediaxPsychological aspectsxUnited States. 0aMass mediaxPsychological aspects. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814770153423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814770153.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK